channel.title: CVE Feed for ASUS -- RT-AX88U
channel.description: The latest CVEs for ASUS -- RT-AX88U

item.title: CVE-2022-26674|2024-08-03T05:11:44.783Z -- asus -- rt-ax88u
item.description: ASUS RT-AX88U has a Format String vulnerability, which allows an unauthenticated remote attacker to write to arbitrary memory address and perform remote arbitrary code execution, arbitrary system operation or disrupt service.

item.title: CVE-2022-26673|2024-08-03T05:11:44.364Z -- asus -- rt-ax88u
item.description: ASUS RT-AX88U has insufficient filtering for special characters in the HTTP header parameter. A remote attacker with general user privilege can exploit this vulnerability to inject JavaScript and perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks.
